Our Services






            Types of Services
          Heading link



 
Copy link








We offer a variety of services designed to provide different types of support. These services fall into two categories:
• Services that you can access immediately or sign up for online
• Services that require you to call our office (312-996-3490) and schedule an initial consultation








            Services that You Can Access Immediately or Sign Up for Online
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Resource Library
                    

                Check out our collection of apps, worksheets, and informational materials
            









                            Single-Session Appointments
                    

                Schedule a brief consultation online to solve a specific problem or learn more about our services
            









                            Virtual Drop-In Spaces
                    

                Register online to get support and learn skills on an as-needed basis
            









                            Workshops
                    

                Register online to learn more information and build skills to improve your mental health
            









                            Mind-Body Programs
                    

                Register online for a deeper dive into specific coping skills like mindfulness and self-compassion
            









                            Peer Support Groups
                    

                Register online to connect with other UIC students and improve your mental health
            









                            Crisis Services
                    

                Call the Counseling Center at (312) 996-3490 to receive 24/7 crisis services
            









                            Community Provider Database
                    

                Looking for mental health services outside of UIC? Check out our online database of providers.
            









            Services that Require an Initial Consultation
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                            Group Therapy
                    

                Weekly long-term therapy groups with other students who share similar identities and experiences
            









                            Brief Relationship Therapy
                    

                Weekly therapy for two or more clients who are in a relationship with each other
            









                            Brief Individual Therapy
                    

                Weekly one-on-one therapy with a Counseling Center staff member
            









                            Psychiatry
                    

                Consultation and prescriptions for medication to address mental health concerns
            









                            Case Management
                    

                Some students benefit from longer-term or more specialized mental health services in the community. Our case managers can help you find the right fit.
            










            What Service Might Be Right for Me?
          Heading link



 
Copy link



It’s okay if you’re not sure what service will help you the most – an initial consultation counselor can help you with that! But if you’d like to get an idea, these questions can help.





                            Do I need coping skills or a space to process my thoughts and feelings?
                    








            Coping vs Processing
          




            Coping Skills
          

I want to learn specific strategies and techniques to help improve my mental health.





      Resource Library
    



      Nod App
    



      Single-Session Appointments
    



      Virtual Drop-In Spaces
    



      Mind Body Programs
    



      Peer Support
    



      Workshops
    






            Process Thoughts/Feelings
          

I want to talk through what’s on my mind.





      Single-Session Appointments
    



      Virtual Drop-In Spaces
    



      Peer Support
    



      Group Therapy
    



      Brief Relationship Therapy
    



      Brief Individual Therapy
    












                            Do I have specific goals in mind or do I want more open-ended support?
                    








            Goal-Directed vs. Open-Ended
          




            Goal-Directed
          

I can think of one or two specific things I’d like to work on.





      Resource Library
    



      Nod App
    



      Single-Session Appointments
    



      Mind Body Programs
    



      Workshops
    



      Virtual Drop-In Spaces
    



      Brief Relationship Therapy
    



      Brief Individual Therapy
    






            Open-Ended
          

I may have some goals in mind, but would prefer something a bit more flexible.





      Virtual Drop-In Spaces
    



      Peer Support
    



      Group Therapy
    



      Case Management
    












                            Could medication be right for me?
                    








            Psychiatry
          

Your initial consultation counselor might recommend that you consult with a psychiatrist, who can help you learn about and manage your medication options.



      Psychiatry
    









                            Am I looking for support on an as-needed basis or a regular weekly commitment?
                    








            As-Needed vs. Commitment
          




            As-Needed
          

I prefer flexibility.





      Resource Library
    



      Nod App
    



      Single-Session Appointments
    



