      Brief Individual Therapy
    












                            Do I work best on my own, one-on-one, or in groups?
                    








            Number of People Involved
          




            On My Own
          

I prefer to do things myself, and I’m not sure I want to share much about myself in order to get help.





      Resource Library
    



      Nod App
    



      Mind Body Services
    



      Workshops
    






            One-On-One
          

I’d like to talk with someone else.





      Single-Session Appointments
    



      Brief Relationship Therapy
    



      Brief Individual Therapy
    






            In Groups
          

It helps to know that I’m not alone.





      Virtual Drop-In Spaces
    



      Peer Support
    



      Group Therapy
    












                            Would I benefit from a longer-term connection to a therapist?
                    








            Longer-Term Treatment Options
          

Some students benefit from connecting with a therapist who providers longer-term or more open-ended services than we do. If you are looking to establish a longer-term relationship, we can help you find the right fit outside of UIC.





            I Can Figure That Out
          

Explore our community provider database.





      Community Provider Database
    






            I Need Help With That
          

Finding the right provider and navigating insurance (or lack of insurance) can be hard. Our case managers can help you find the right fit.





      Case Management
    

















            Disclaimer
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Please note that these questions and answers are for educational use only and are not a substitute for individualized referrals or recommendations from a mental health professional. For more help determining which services might be right for you, call us at (312) 996-3490 to schedule an initial consultation or schedule a single-session appointment online now.





